This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category as it proposes techniques to reduce the sample complexity of deep reinforcement learning for continuous control tasks. It also explores the use of learned models for accelerating model-free reinforcement learning, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO) categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of simulated robotic control tasks, which could also place it in the systems and control (cs.SY) category. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with continuous control tasks that may involve visual inputs.
